  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support in transmission containment and reduction of related mortality of Cholera disease in 147 LGAs across 10 states in Nigeria.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving health assistance to vulnerable communities affected by, or at risk of, cholera in Adamawa, Bauchi, Borno, Jigawa, Katsina, Kano, Kebbi, Sokoto, Yobe, and Zamfara. This WHO project deploys rapid response teams, investigates suspected cases of cholera, establishes cholera treatment centres, and raises awareness in communities about infection prevention and control. The project provides life-saving assistance to 164,000 people, including 37,000 women, 31,000 men, 96,000 children, and 1,800 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
